  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Acute subcutaneous abdominal wound-healing impairment after surgical intervention

          -  Sizes of wound opening (maximum diameter ≥ 3 cm)

          -  Wound surface ≥ 9 qcm

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Lack of infrastructure for outpatient continuation of treatment and study-specific
        interventions

          -  Existence of an open abdominal fascia

          -  Acute serious organ failure

          -  Application of an other active vacuum device at the wound treated during the study
             conduct within 8 days before screening visit

          -  Ongoing / during 3 weeks after chemo therapy

          -  Ongoing / during 3 weeks after radiation therapy Contraindications in accordance with
             the safety precautions issued by the FDA or the companies
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
